<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[189,797,1689,1929]" lastBlockId="1.[835,1443,1149,1929]" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">
On the very same day when the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Teslenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[189,326,1726,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Megaperlodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiunovi">
<emphasis box="[189,326,1726,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">M. tiunovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published, the first author encountered a color photograph of a similar stonefly in the recent monograph of Korean Orthoptera (
<bibRefCitation author="Kim, T. W." box="[337,456,1833,1857]" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" refId="ref1183" refString="Kim, T. W. 2013. Orthoptera of Korea. National Institute of Biological Resources, Incheon, Republic of Korea. 381 pp. (in Korean)" type="book" year="2013">Kim 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The image is included in a table to present orders related to Orthoptera, but even though it is small, the characteristic wing and head pattern of the species are obvious. Dr. Tae Woo Kim kindly provided us an original, larger image and informed us about the habitat and other circumstances where the photo was taken. Unfortunately, the specimen was not captured, but it was clearly identical with the 
<typeStatus box="[1257,1309,1330,1354]" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">type</typeStatus>
series. Dr 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Teslenko" authorityName="A. Teslenko" box="[835,1148,1365,1389]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Valentina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Valentina A. Teslenko</taxonomicName>
also confirmed its conspecificity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[835,1443,1149,1929]" lastBlockId="2.[189,798,228,396]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">
Although it is not the usual practice to publish stonefly records without voucher specimens, vertebrate biologists occasionally do, [e.g. birds, where even a new species was described without fixing 
<typeStatus box="[913,965,1582,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">type</typeStatus>
specimens 
<bibRefCitation author="Robb, M. &amp; A. B. van der Berg &amp; M. Constantine" box="[1106,1319,1581,1605]" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" pagination="275 - 310" refId="ref1317" refString="Robb, M., A. B. van der Berg, &amp; M. Constantine. 2013. A new species of Strix owl from Oman. Dutch Birding, 35 (5): 275 - 310." type="journal article" year="2013">Robb et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
; however, disputed and put in synonymy by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirwan, G. M. &amp; M. Schweizer &amp; J. L. Copete" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" pagination="28 - 50" refId="ref1214" refString="Kirwan, G. M., M. Schweizer, &amp; J. L. Copete 2015. Multiple lines of evidence confirm that Hume's Owl Strix butleri (A. O. Hume, 1878) is two species, with description of an unnamed species (Aves: Non-Passeriformes: Strigidae). Zootaxa, 3904 (1): 28 - 50." type="journal article" year="2015">Kirwan et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
]. We take this exception because of the distinctive habitus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Teslenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[1103,1224,1690,1713]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Megaperlodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiunovi">
<emphasis box="[1103,1224,1690,1713]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">M. tiunovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the detailed agreement based on high quality photographs of the Korean specimen (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1172,1761,1785]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[189,230,1041,1065]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,290,995]" captionTargetId="figure-356@1.[286,1344,290,995]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Habitus of Megaperlodes tiunovi Teslenko 2015 from South Korea (photograph by T.W. Kim)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4757709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4757709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) with that of the 
<typeStatus box="[1391,1443,1761,1785]" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">type</typeStatus>
specimens (
<figureCitation box="[975,1083,1797,1821]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStartId-0="1.[189,230,1041,1065]" captionStartId-1="2.[189,226,1377,1401]" captionTargetBox-0="[286,1344,290,995]" captionTargetBox-1="[286,1344,470,1330]" captionTargetId-0="figure-356@1.[286,1344,290,995]" captionTargetId-1="figure-291@2.[286,1344,470,1331]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="Fig. 1. Habitus of Megaperlodes tiunovi Teslenko 2015 from South Korea (photograph by T.W. Kim)." captionText-1="Fig. 2. Distribution of the genus Megaperlodes Yokoyama, Isobe &amp; Yamamoto 1990; gray areas are above 2000 meters; open circles = M. tiunovi; closed circles = M. niger." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4757709" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4757711" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4757709/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4757711/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="127">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
, 4 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Teslenko, V. A." box="[1153,1326,1797,1821]" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" pagination="553 - 562" refId="ref1508" refString="Teslenko, V. A. 2015. A new species of Megaperlodes Yokoyama et al. 1990 (Plecoptera, Perlodidae) from the South of the Russian Far East. Zootaxa, 3904 (4): 553 - 562." type="journal article" year="2015">Teslenko 2015</bibRefCitation>
). We also note that color photography has increasing importance in the study of stoneflies, and photographic guides are already available (
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; S. W. Szczytko &amp; C. R. Nelson" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="1" pageNumber="127" refId="ref1461" refString="Stark, B. P., S. W. Szczytko, &amp; C. R. Nelson. 1998. American Stoneflies: A Photographic Guide to the Plecoptera. The Caddis Press, Columbus, Ohio, USA. iv + 126 pp." type="book" year="1998">Stark et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Szczytko, S. W. &amp; B. C. Kondratieff" box="[290,631,228,252]" pageId="2" pageNumber="128" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref1358" refString="Szczytko, S. W. &amp; B. C. Kondratieff. 2015. A Photographic Atlas of the eastern Nearctic Isoperlinae (Plecoptera: Perlidae) species. Monographs of Illiesia, 2: 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="2015">Szczytko &amp; Kondratieff 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,798,228,396]" lastBlockId="2.[835,1443,228,396]" pageId="2" pageNumber="128">
The Korean specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Teslenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[536,657,265,288]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Megaperlodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiunovi">
<emphasis box="[536,657,265,288]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="128">M. tiunovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found near a narrow stream resting on stones during daytime and showed weak flight ability. According to the latest stonefly reports from 
<collectingCountry box="[642,796,372,396]" name="South Korea" pageId="2" pageNumber="128">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Muranyi, D. &amp; S. J. Park" box="[843,1114,228,252]" pageId="2" pageNumber="128" pagination="70 - 85" refId="ref1281" refString="Muranyi, D. &amp; S. J. Park. 2011. Contribution to the fall stonefly (Plecoptera) fauna of Korea. Illiesia, 7 (6): 70 - 85." type="journal article" year="2011">Murányi &amp; Park 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P. &amp; R. W. Baumann" box="[1130,1430,228,252]" pageId="2" pageNumber="128" pagination="148 - 155" refId="ref1640" refString="Zwick, P. &amp; R. W. Baumann. 2011. Nemoura jejudoensis a new species of stonefly and the redescription of Amphinemura baei Ham and Lee (Plecoptera, Nemouridae) from Jeju Island, Korea. Illiesia, 7 (15): 148 - 155." type="journal article" year="2011">Zwick &amp; Baumann 2011</bibRefCitation>
), this is the 62th species reported from the country. To explain this range extension we provide a map on the known distribution of the two 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Megaperlodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1295,1443,336,360]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="128">Megaperlodes</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[934,1001,372,396]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[189,226,1377,1401]" captionTargetBox="[286,1344,470,1330]" captionTargetId="figure-291@2.[286,1344,470,1331]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Distribution of the genus Megaperlodes Yokoyama, Isobe &amp; Yamamoto 1990; gray areas are above 2000 meters; open circles = M. tiunovi; closed circles = M. niger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4757711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4757711/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="128">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
